Wash and dry all produce. Core, deseed, and finely dice @bell pepper{1}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1} (for 4 servings, zest 1 lemon and quarter both). Drain and rinse @kidney beans{13.4%ounce}.

In a small #pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a medium #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and scallion whites; cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir in garlic; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir beans, @veggie stock concentrate{1%unit}, @smoked paprika{1%teaspoon}, 1/4 cup water (1/3 cup for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} into pot with veggies. Bring mixture to a simmer, then reduce heat to low. Cook until thickened, ~{7-8%minutes}. Turn off heat; stir in 1 TBSP @butter{2%tablespoon} and season with salt and pepper. Cover to keep warm.

Meanwhile, pat @Regal Springs tilapia{11%ounce} dry with paper towels; season all over with salt and pepper. Rub both sides of each fillet with @blackening spice{1%tablespoon}. Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in a large, preferably nonstick, #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add tilapia and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

In a small #bowl{}, combine @sour cream{2%tablespoon} with @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} to taste. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in lemon zest and 1 TBSP butter (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice, beans, and tilapia between plates. Top with crema and scallion greens. Serve with lemon wedges on the side.

> Cue the brass band, because your taste buds are about to take a trip to the Big Easy! We're talking blackened tilapia and saucy, smoky red beans piled atop fluffy, lemon-scented rice. It's all finished with a drizzle of spicy crema and some extra hot sauce, if you're really looking to have a wild night. Now if we could only perfect our Hurricane cocktail...